Chelsea forward, Willian, has hinted that he could leave or stay at Stamford Bridge after attracting transfer interest from Arsenal and Manchester United. Willian appeared certain to leave Chelsea when his contract expires at the end of this season. DAILY POST recalls that the Brazilian international recently agreed on a short-term deal to see out the remainder of the campaign with the Blues. Speaking on his future at Chelsea, Willian told the club’s official website: “I want to finish the season well if I go, or maybe I can stay. “I don’t know but what I want now is to play well and for Chelsea to finish in the top four.” Willian added: “We know teams that come from behind want to win to go in the top four as well, so we have to do our job.”